notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-19T12:00:00.044Z",maintainer-agent,"Implemented: @types/node declared as optional peerDependency (>=22, matching the engines floor) with peerDependenciesMeta; SDK.md Install section documents the TS-consumer requirement + moduleResolution guidance. Shipped JSDoc defect CLASS fixed at source: all 26 glued-template docstrings (\"closethe/openthe/blockedthe/defaultthe/... record\") replaced with accurate per-field docs across types.ts, sdk/runtime.ts, runtime-schema.ts, item-types-file.ts, type-workflows.ts, extension surfaces, calendar/plan/context/stats; the three legacy `--path` JSDoc references now cite --pm-path. Packed-tarball TS consumer smoke added to scripts/smoke-npx-from-pack.mjs: real npm-pack tarball installed into a fresh consumer project, strict nodenext tsc -p typecheck of an @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk import using repo-local typescript+@types/node (registry-independent); covering mocked spec extended incl. tsc-failure path."
  "2026-07-19T12:41:30.865Z",maintainer-agent,"Follow-up correction from packed-consumer proof: optional peerDependencies do not install @types/node for a plain npm consumer. The final implementation declares @types/node >=22 as a runtime dependency and the smoke resolves types only from the consumer node_modules; the masking repository typeRoots path was removed."
